      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Once the government gains the authority to define \"misinformation\" or \"hate speech,\" the definition itself becomes a political weapon wielded by the ruling power. Today's \"harmful\" content can easily become tomorrow's political dissent, allowing the state to silence opposition under the guise of maintaining order. This gradual expansion of regulatory power is the classic slippery slope, where minor infringements pave the road directly to totalitarian control over public discourse.",
      "source": "target",
